feedbacktext: I enjoyed the experiment. I'm not too confident in my ability to correctly identify types of birds, dogs, snakes or monkeys and I think this led me to both underestimate my own scores and overestimate the other participant's scores. In particular, my natural instinct was to think he did better than me when I felt that I might have gotten a very low score. I thought about the predictions in more depth, however, as I took seriously the direction to use the scores each round to get better at predicting. I thought the directions were clear and I do think I was able to objectively make predictions and found that I was fairly close on several occasions.

I'm not too confident in my ability to correctly identify types of birds, dogs, snakes or monkeys and I think this led me to both underestimate my own scores and overestimate the other participant's scores. In particular, my natural instinct was to think he did better than me when I felt that I might have gotten a very low score. I thought about the predictions in more depth, however, as I took seriously the direction to use the scores each round to get better at predicting. I thought the directions were clear and I do think I was able to objectively make predictions and found that I was fairly close on several occasions.
